security-center (1.6.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security hardening release
  * Patched dependency vulnerabilities (bytes, quinn-proto, rustls-webpki, rand)
  * Added centralized input validation for protocols, port names, systemctl actions
  * Validated firewalld rich rule construction against protocol allowlist
  * Added config file size limits and JSON sanitization
  * Added pkexec parameter allowlisting
  * Replaced custom version parser with semver
  * Added GitHub Actions CI with audit, deny, clippy, and tests
  * Expanded test coverage from 5 to 31 tests
  * Added accessibility tooltips to chart widgets
  * Hardened logging to avoid path leakage
  * Removed unused dependencies

 -- Christos Daggas <chrisdaggas@example.com>  Thu, 24 Apr 2026 19:30:00 +0300

security-center (1.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Cross-distro support for Fedora, Ubuntu, Debian and all desktop environments
  * Fixed Debian/Ubuntu package dependencies (polkit package naming)
  * KDE Plasma compatibility for accent color detection
  * Config directory renamed from gnome-security-center to security-center
  * Automatic settings migration from old config path
  * Universal autostart desktop entry for all DEs
  * AppImage now bundles GTK4/libadwaita shared libraries
  * Architecture-independent AppImage build
  * Clear error message when PolicyKit is not installed

 -- Christos Daggas <chrisdaggas@example.com>  Thu, 10 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0200

security-center (1.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Consolidated port view — same-port entries grouped into single rows
  * Improved firewall state display (Active, Panic Mode, Inactive)
  * Traffic switch disabled when firewall is stopped
  * Dashboard status syncs after Quick Actions changes
  * Fixed restart button stretching and signal feedback loops

